Governor Ahmadu Fintiri has approved the constitution of a Technical Committee for verification of Local Government Pensioners in Adamawa state. Mr Joab Haggai Sahma is to serve as Chairman, Luqman Mohammed, Secretary, while Mr Kefas James Tagwi, Mr Birma Elkanah  and  Aishatu Mohammed as members. Mr Humwashi Wonosikou, Press Secretary in a statement said the Committee is empowered to coopt 10 other members made up of four from Nigerian Union of Teachers, (NUT) and the Nigerian Union of Local Government Employees (NULGE). Two other members would be produced by Ministry for Local Government Affairs and Local Government Pension Board will while there may be a need for other auxiliary staff to facilitate the work of the committee. Fintiri congratulated members of the committee for finding them worthy and urged them to ensure decorum in the discharge of their duty. 